{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"510f4718-23a4-44f8-883f-43fbc05a053b","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, preserving your reason message.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4390552c-2b6f-43ae-aa1f-61e1367973f1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question - no tools needed.","outputTokens":304,"requestId":"0BC7:1A4FD7:565AEB:648159:69F00971"},"id":"b0fd8dcb-cf33-4757-bb67-2308118fb8bd","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:12:23.550Z","parentId":"b85193b9-2866-4397-be6d-5ffb65d14f24"}
